gomodel:SYNGO_5520  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 3: In hippocampal neurons from AP-2u (gene Ap2m1) knockout mice, the ablated expression of the AP-2 complex was shown to result in defective endocytosis of VGLUT1-labeled synaptic vesicles (SV).\n\nWhile no comparable data is available for the alpha-adaptin subunits of the clathrin adaptor AP-2, it has been shown that;\n- AP2A is involved in SV endocytosis in C.elegans (PMID:23482940) and Drosophila (PMID:9118220)\n- AP2A1 and AP2A2 are both abundant in mammalian synaptic vesicles (PMID:33376223)\n\nTaken together, we here annotate AP2A1 as involved in synaptic vesicle endocytosis. Experimental description: Result text; \"We conditionally ablated AP-2 expression by tamoxifen induction of Cre recombinase in hippocampal neurons from Ap2m1lox/lox mice crossed with\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2023-11-03" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_5520" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .
